HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 904
By Jones R
A RESOLUTION to recognize and congratulate Analee Shaver,
Miss Tennessee's Teen 2025.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those emerging community
leaders who strive to improve the quality of life for their fellow citizens while bringing beauty,
grace, and purpose to all their endeavors; and
WHEREAS, one such superlative individual is Analee Shaver of Collierville, the 2025
title holder for the Miss Tennessee's Teen, a most befitting honor, as it recognizes her
dedication to excellence and her devotion to serving her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Shaver is a student at Collierville High School, where she has served in
various leadership roles; in addition to being actively involved in Best Buddies and Diamond
Girls clubs, she is a member of the Varsity Pom Team, which recently garnered second place in
the Large Varsity Hip Hop competition at the 2025 UDA National Dance Team Championship;
and
WHEREAS, Analee Shaver's dance achievements also include being named Rookie of
the Year with the Rebel Royals Varsity Dance Team and earning the highest-scoring solo
performance for ages eleven and up at the 2022 Encore DCS Regional Competition; and
WHEREAS, a dancer for fourteen years, she brought grace and emotion to the stage
during pageant competition with her lyrical performance to "Ashes" by Celine Dion; and
WHEREAS, Analee Shaver has shown exceptional dedication to her community service
initiative of Stand4Me, which empowers students to become peer advocates for those
experiencing bullying; through this initiative, she encourages inclusion, empathy, and
confidence among students of all backgrounds; and
HJR0904
012843
- 1 -

WHEREAS, after graduating from high school and attending college, her ultimate goal is
to become a speech language pathologist, specializing in working with children who experience
speech impediments; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Shaver is an exceptional role model and community leader, and it is
fitting that we recognize her worthy reign as Miss Tennessee's Teen 2025; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend and congratulate Analee Shaver, Miss Tennessee's Teen
2025, extending our best wishes for her success during her ambassadorial year and in all her
future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
